# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Public-release boundary
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The framework repository is code-only. The journal manuscript, AIHealth
# conference camera-ready, aggregate result tables, internal planning notes,
# and reviewer-feedback drafts all live under these paths locally but are not
# redistributed publicly. They are kept on disk so authors can keep working
# without re-creating them, but git will not track them.

paper/
submissions/
reports/
download.zip
download.zip.txt

# Keep two canonical methodology docs in the public release; exclude
# everything else under docs/ (internal planning, reviewer-feedback,
# superseded drafts, work-package outlines).
docs/*
!docs/ADNI_LABEL_ONTOLOGY.md
!docs/DATA_ACCESS.md
docs/reviews/

# AIHealth conference-submission tooling is not part of the framework.
scripts/build_aihealth_template_docx.py
scripts/render_aihealth_camera_ready_pdf.py

# Pre-merge redirect stubs (superseded by docs/SPLITGUARD_AD_FORWARD_PLAN.md
# which itself is kept local).
MASTER_PLAN.md
SPLITGUARD_AD_SCOPE.md
download.zip
